  <bioghist id="aspace_ecdbc52d2c0a575569e1e7b83f27de69">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>William Henry Miller (1848-1922), was a student of the Cornell University College of Architecture from 1868 to 1870, later becoming a prominent Ithaca, New York architect. He designed several buildings on the Cornell University campus.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_310c025d7baec82014903a32c2c3065a">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Drawings, photographs (positive and negative), plans, and specifications of Ithaca and Cornell buildings by Miller, list of newspaper articles concerning Miller and notable architecture in Ithaca (1870-1917), and a biographical sketch of Miller by Dethlefsen.</p>  </scopecontent>
